In order to fix this [bug|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-6404], Confluence copied over *all* user to *USERINFO* during the upgrade process.

However this process will cause Confluence to display every single user registered into its "People Directory". This may not be a good solution for customers that retrieve all users from LDAP but does not provide the permission to login to Confluence, hence inactive or unlicensed user.

It would be great if Confluence is able to hide those user to ensure that People Directory only display valid user

